trong data-start="8" data-end="40">not inside every Python file</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="43" data-end="138">This is one of the biggest differences between a beginner's GitHub repo and a professional one.</p>
<h2 data-section-id="11rlvx8" data-start="140" data-end="164">What professionals do</h2>
<p data-start="166" data-end="188">Each Python file gets:</p>
<ul data-start="189" data-end="289">
<li data-section-id="n5nn79" data-start="189" data-end="227">
<p data-start="191" data-end="227">A short module docstring at the top.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1ddedm3" data-start="228" data-end="251">
<p data-start="230" data-end="251">Well-named functions.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="xbmvp" data-start="252" data-end="289">
<p data-start="254" data-end="289">Comments only where they add value.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="291" data-end="338">The <strong data-start="295" data-end="308">README.md</strong> explains the overall project.</p>
<hr data-start="340" data-end="343">
