<hr data-start="1809" data-end="1812">
<h2 data-section-id="1yanudo" data-start="1814" data-end="1851">What impresses recruiters the most</h2>
<p data-start="1853" data-end="1936">The descriptions are nice, but <strong data-start="1884" data-end="1918">documentation and organization</strong> matter even more.</p>
<p data-start="1938" data-end="1993">Once we finish this repository, I want to help you add:</p>
<ul data-start="1995" data-end="2195">
<li data-section-id="13hmou5" data-start="1995" data-end="2020">
<p data-start="1997" data-end="2020">📈 Architecture diagram</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1pusu49" data-start="2021" data-end="2042">
<p data-start="2023" data-end="2042">📊 Workflow diagram</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="14mk86w" data-start="2043" data-end="2078">
<p data-start="2045" data-end="2078">📸 Screenshots of the ETL running</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="bindj4" data-start="2079" data-end="2101">
<p data-start="2081" data-end="2101">📋 Example SQL MERGE</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="ow46iq" data-start="2102" data-end="2118">
<p data-start="2104" data-end="2118">📁 Sample data</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="3uhez3" data-start="2119" data-end="2156">
<p data-start="2121" data-end="2156">🚀 GitHub Actions (automated tests)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="f4974v" data-start="2157" data-end="2172">
<p data-start="2159" data-end="2172">🧪 Unit tests</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="5cum1f" data-start="2173" data-end="2195">
<p data-start="2175" data-end="2195">📝 A polished README</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2197" data-end="2298">Those additions make the project look much more like something maintained by an experienced engineer.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="myeteg" data-start="2300" data-end="2328">One thing I also noticed</h3>
<p data-start="2330" data-end="2702" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">All seven of your loaders are still almost identical. That's okay for now, but the <strong data-start="2413" data-end="2442">next improvement I'd make</strong> is to refactor them so each loader is only about <strong data-start="2492" data-end="2507">20–30 lines</strong> and simply calls the shared <code data-start="2536" data-end="2544">common</code> modules. That kind of code reuse is something recruiters and engineering managers often notice because it demonstrates maintainability and thoughtful design.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start"><div aria-label="Response actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none touch:w-[calc(100%+--spacing(3.5))] -mt-1 w-[calc(100%+--spacing(2.5))] duration-[1.5s] focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto pointer-events-none [mask-image:linear-gradient(to_right,black_33%,transparent_66%)] [mask-size:300%_100%] [mask-position:100%_0%] motion-safe:transition-[mask-position] group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:[mask-position:0_0]" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface-hover rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy response" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-c74d0474.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface